cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with resource allocation in small cell networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses interference management, which is a topic related to signal processing and multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a hierarchical scheme to tackle computational complexity, which could be related to distributed computing (cs.DC).
